4 (8) Any person found by the commission to have committed a violation of this code
5 may appeal the action to the Franklin Circuit Court. The appeal shall be initiated
6 within thirty (30) days after the date of the final action of the commission by filing
7 a petition with the court against the commission. The commission shall transmit to
8 the clerk of the court all evidence considered by the commission at the public
9 hearing. The court shall hear the appeal upon the record as certified by the
10 commission.
